The handbook and the span-expert agent both carry the born-stale-prevention rule: commit a span only once every file it anchors is committed (clean against HEAD, verified with a git status --short check), because git span add hashes each anchor against HEAD. The agent operationalizes it and the two handbook sections teach it; all three must state the same rule.
